inv:Dataset.inv:Title: Payments over £500
inv:Dataset.inv:Description:
Payments made to suppliers where the invoice total amounts to over £500.  Note that a single invoice may be represented by multiple lines in the payment data and as such some lines may contain amounts under £500.

Some data may appear as Redacted Personal Data. This personal data is protected by the Data Protection Act 1998 to prevent any individual being identified.

This data will be published in the middle of each following month. So data for October is published mid November and so on. This is simply to allow us to run the appropriate data gathering exercise.

inv:Dataset.inv:Title: Budget
inv:Dataset.inv:Description:
The budget which the Council is working to for the financial year and has been agreed by the full Council meeting. This excludes unallocated contigencies.

The Council’s Revenue Budget for 2011/12 is £200.6 million which, when compared to the equivalent figure for 2010/11, is a decrease in spending of £9.5 million (4.5%).  Spending reductions have primarily been driven by the significant funding cuts imposed across the public sector by Central Government.  In meeting this challenge and in order to deliver a freeze in Council Tax the authority has given its highest priority to identifying and delivering savings through back office support and/or efficiency measures wherever this has been possible.
